[Sydney NSWContaminated Land Auditor ( Job Number: AAP010RV ) Primary Location : AU-AU-Sydney
Description
Opportunity to lead and further develop a successful business whilst building a professional profile and reputation, for self and for Arcadis, in the industry
Flexible work options
National leadership role based in Sydney
What are we looking for?

We are currently looking for an experienced senior leader that will be responsible nationally for the continued growth and success of our team in Sydney. Your role will include:
Managing and leading (with the support of local Team Leaders), a national business, delivering services involving contaminated site audit;
Carrying out assigned activities including investigation, assessment, analysis and reporting in accordance with NSW and National Legislation;
Providing resolution of technical issues on projects and working in collaboration with other sectors/disciplines to ensure the integrity of projects;
Maintaining ongoing communication with discipline leaders and clients when required, to ensure effective communication on matters relevant to projects;
Building a profile with clients and within the industry to keep up-to-date with innovations and developments which will develop innovative and entrepreneurial thinking and behavior;
Managing and leading a team of professionals, including line management responsibility and financial responsibility for an independent profit & loss account; and
Keeping up to date with technical and legislative developments and seek opportunities to develop professional profile such as giving presentations to conferences/meetings/professional bodies and participation in technical committees for trade organisations and standards
Qualifications
Who are we looking for?

You will have:
Relevant engineering degree in Environmental Science/Engineering, Geology/Hydrogeology or Chemistry with Chartered status or equivalent professional accreditation;
15+ years’ demonstrated industry experience working on audited contaminated site investigations in New South Wales;
EPA accreditation as Contaminated Land Auditor in NSW; Accreditation with additional states a bonus;
Extensive experience in field investigations, particularly soil and groundwater sampling, groundwater well installation and drilling supervision, along with air quality monitoring (PM2.5, PM10, asbestos);
Experience in reporting and data management, including Preliminary Site Investigations, Sampling and Analysis Quality Plans, Detailed Site Investigations, Risk Assessments, Geographical Information Systems, Esdat and groundwater modelling programs;
Experience in project management, business development, client management are highly desirable;
Demonstrated technical, commercial and delivery acumen; and
Recognised leader in specialist discipline with well-established industry networks.

Who are we?

Arcadis is the leading design & consultancy firm for natural and built assets with a passion to improve the quality of life and be recognised as the best. To achieve this, we collaborate with the 27,000 Arcadians in over 350 offices around the globe on world-changing projects.

With skilled and talented people on-board, we provide major companies and governments around the globe with ground-breaking design, consultancy, engineering, business advisory, architecture and project management expertise.

Why work for us?

We are an award-winning company that offers all Arcadians flexible work arrangements, attractive salaries, global growth opportunities and both formal and informal career development training. As an equal opportunity employer, we value and promote diversity at Arcadis and strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.
2018 WGEA Equal Opportunity Employer of Choice for Gender Equality
2018 Great Place to Work certified employer
2017 Flex Able certified employer
What now?

Visit our careers page for more information or to apply: www.arcadis.com/applynow Job : Specialists & scientists]

