[Brisbane QLDCutting edge CMO
Highly attractive remuneration package
Great team culture
Luina Bio, one of Australia’s most experienced biopharmaceutical contract manufacturing organisations (CMO), is focused on serving the global pharmaceutical, biotechnology and veterinary industries. Drawing on more than 20 years of contract manufacturing experience, Luina Bio scientists have the expertise, training and experience to ensure a successful outcome in the manufacture of both biopharmaceutical and live microbial drugs. The scope of their capability ranges from the manufacture of recombinant proteins, live therapeutics, whole cell vaccines, viral vaccines, purified plant extracts, and pro-biotics for pre-clinical; to phase 1 to 3 human clinical trials and commercial product for veterinary clients both within Australia and internationally.

Reporting to the Quality Manager, the Quality Control Manager will manage all aspects of the Quality Control team and laboratory activities in accordance with GMP standards. Their charter will be to ensure adequate systems are in place to support all aspects of Quality Control, while leading, motivating and managing the Quality Control team to achieve targets. Due to their continued growth and internal restructures, they now seek the services of an experienced and motivated Quality Control Manager to join the team.

The Position:

Provide leadership, direction and development to the Quality Control team;
Develop strategic planning initiatives to achieve continuous improvement within the Quality Control systems at Luina Bio;
Manage adherence to all aspects of GLP and GMP;
Review all final quality control data for accuracy and completeness;
Approve all documents, materials and product investigations in line with agreed procedures;
Liaise with clients and project teams to support decision making in regards to quality control testing;
Review and approve validation protocols and reporting;
Compile management reports and conduct internal quality audits in line with regulatory requirements;
Participate in all external audits.
The Person:

Degree qualifications in Microbiology, Science or related discipline essential;
Minimum 10 years’ experience working in quality role in the pharmaceutical or biotechnology related industry highly desirable, with at least 5 years’ management experience;
Proven experience in developing and writing Standard Operating Procedures;
Thorough understanding of the requirements of regulatory bodies including the TGA or equivalent for conduct and recording of work;
Experience in the maintenance of quality systems, including auditing, deviations, change control and document control;
Knowledge and understanding of the principles of quality and GMP/GLP
Enthusiastic problem solver, people motivator;
Ethical leader with strong partnership orientation;
Open minded and willing to openly share thoughts and information.
Luina Bio are committed attracting and retaining talented individuals to join their highly focused team. They offer a very generous salary package in return for dedication and professionalism. If you are a values driven professional who is excited by the challenges of working in a dynamic, growing organisation, please apply online at www.bluhat.com.au. Your confidentiality is assured.]

